            . I am a <rs id="t18190217-102-viclabel600" type="occupation">hair-dresser</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18190217-102-victim947 t18190217-102-viclabel600"></join>, and live in Charles-court. On the 25th of January, about nine o'clock at night, I was in <placeName id="t18190217-102-crimeloc601">Newport-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18190217-102-crimeloc601" type="placeName" value="Newport-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18190217-102-crimeloc601" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18190217-102-off598 t18190217-102-crimeloc601"></join>, a mob was collected; I went up, stood there about two minutes, and missed my apron and things out of my pocket - the prisoner was immediately secured with them.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18190217-102-person949">
                  WILLIAM 
                  HODGKISSON
               <interp inst="t18190217-102-person949" type="surname" value="HODGKISSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190217-102-person949" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190217-102-person949" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was passing along Newport-street, and saw the prisoner put his hand into Ring's pocket, and take something out, which I thought was a handkerchief. I told the prosecutor, and secured him. I saw him give the things to another person in the crowd.</p>
               <p>
